The paper deals with the problem of preventing double-spending in blockchain-based algorithms, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the security aspects of the asset transfer problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with the consensus number of the asset transfer object, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the message passing setting with Byzantine players, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
